    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Engine Electrical Components - Description of Engine Electrical Components -
        Engine Mounted - ICP Sensor (Injection Control Pressure)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26510.2.9" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ICP Sensor (Injection Control Pressure)</title>
        <figure id="e3001111" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ09/J09017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>ICP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>A micro strain gauge sensor installed through the right side valve cover in the oil rail. The ECM monitors
            the ICP signal to determine the injection control pressure for engine operation. The ICP signal is used to
            control the IPR valve. The ICP sensor provides feedback to the ECM for Closed Loop ICP control.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
